text: Trachicaranx tersus is an extinct, prehistoric jackfish from Turkmenistan that lived in an ocean upwelling. Some incomplete fossil specimens were once identified as "Uylyaichthys eugeniae." == Description == This fish probably looked like a large pompano with medium-sized eyes. == Related pages == * Asteroid impact avoidance * Boulder * List of fish of Montana * List of prehistoric bony fish genera * Qarmoutus == References == # "Taxonomy Details for Trachicaranx".
